## Context

`hasBranch(id string) bool` in `tickets/tools/go/main.go` has no unit test.
Identified during PR #81 review. The function is the sole claim-check in
`cmdReady` and `cmdGraph` after the branch-as-claim migration (ticket 0066).

## Actions

1. Add a test fixture that initialises a temporary git repo, creates/deletes
   branches, and asserts `hasBranch` returns the correct value.
2. Cover: local branch match, local branch no-match, remote branch match
   (simulated via a second bare repo), and the offline-safe fallback (remote
   check failure treated as no-claim).

## Test

```go
func TestHasBranchLocal(t *testing.T) {
    // init temp repo, create branch "0099-foo", assert hasBranch("0099") == true
    // assert hasBranch("0098") == false
}
```

## Exit criteria

`go test ./tickets/tools/go/...` passes with the new test covering at least
the local-branch true and false cases.
